menus
[TITLE]The Manual:  The Many Menus[/TITLE]
Starting from the main dwarf fortress screen, there are many options, and it can
be difficult to sort things out at first.  Here each choice will be described.
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]General Notes[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Use [IKEY:CURSOR_UP][IKEY:CURSOR_DOWN][IKEY:CURSOR_LEFT][IKEY:CURSOR_RIGHT]
[IKEY:CURSOR_UPLEFT][IKEY:CURSOR_UPRIGHT][IKEY:CURSOR_DOWNLEFT][IKEY:CURSOR_DOWNRIGHT] to move the view window around.
[B]
Use [IKEY:CHANGETAB] to cycle through different arrangements of the view windows.
[B]
Keep in mind that you can pause the game at any time using [IKEY:D_PAUSE].  If you want to step through
the game Very slowly, use [IKEY:D_ONESTEP].  It takes about ten presses of this key for the average dwarf to move one square,
but it lets you watch battles very precisely if you like.
[B]
If you ever get lost as you scroll around, press [IKEY:D_GATE].  This key zooms you to the center of the cliff face.
[B]
Every announcement made at the bottom of the screen is saved for you.  Press [IKEY:D_ANNOUNCE] to view them.
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Placing Buildings[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_BUILDING] to place a building.  Most buildings require some kind of material and a dwarf
with the proper profession settings to build them.  Note that many buildings first need to be designed
by a dwarf with the Architecture profession.  Follow the link for more information.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_make_buildings]Building Placement Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Designations[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_DESIGNATE] to designate areas for digging, detailing, plant gathering and wood cutting.
If a dwarf has the appropriate profession and equipment, work will begin immediately.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_designations]Designation Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]View Units[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_VIEWUNIT] to view unit information.  Move the cursor to a unit and you'll see a menu.
This is where you set professions, view thoughts and wounds, view skills and set soldier preferences,
among other things.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_viewunit]Unit Viewing Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Create Building Tasks[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_BUILDJOB] to view the task lists for your buildings.  You also create rooms and set
some other settings using the menus that arise from this selection.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_buildjob]Building Task Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]View Building Items[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_BUILDITEM] to view the objects that are in a building.  You'll often find objects
you thought were missing inside a building.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_builditem]Building Item Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Stockpiles[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_STOCKPILES] to create a new stockpile.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_stockpiles]Stockpile Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Overall Status[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_STATUS] to view the overall status of your fortress.  You can check your population and
your food stores.  At first you can also get advice and set preferences for your kitchens and animals.
Later on several additional menus open up as you attract specialized dwarves.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_status]Overall Status Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Set Standing Orders[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_ORDERS] to set the standing orders for your dwarves.  Follow the link for descriptions.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_orders]Standing Order Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Room/Building List[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_ROOMS] to view the list of rooms and buildings.  You can also check
how a dwarf values a room from here.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_roomlist]Room List Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Job List[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_JOBLIST] to view a list of jobs.  This is similar to the Unit List screen.  If you have a manager,
you can get to the manager screen from here.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_jobunitlist]Job/Unit List Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Unit List[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_UNITLIST] to view a list of units.  This is similar to the Job List screen.  If you have a manager,
you can get to the manager screen from here.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_jobunitlist]Job/Unit List Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Military[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_MILITARY] to view and change your military.  You can access the menus of individual squads and set the
chain of command from this screen.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_military]Military Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Command Squads[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_SQUADS] to order your squads to station at a new location or to send them on patrols.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_squads]Command Squad Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Look Around[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_LOOK] to look at everything that is in a map square.  You can select many of these objects for further descriptions.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_look]Look Around Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Nobles[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_NOBLES] to view your nobles.  This option is not initially available, but becomes accessible as soon as your first
specialized dwarf arrives.  Most nobles and specialized dwarves look like [C:5:0:0][CHAR:1][C:7:0:0].
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_nobles]Noble Specifics[/LINK]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Civilizations[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_CIVLIST] to view your neighbors.
[B]
[LINK:data\help\menu_civlist]Civilization Specifics[/LINK]
